# Design tokens (required)

This project has a Figma design system. **Always use design tokens** for colors, typography, shadows, and spacing. Do not introduce one-off values unless the user explicitly asks for a design change.

## Token sources

| Source | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `Design-tokens/tokens.json` | Figma export (source of truth) |
| `src/styles/generated-tokens.css` | CSS variables (`--sys-*`, `--ref-*`, `--elevation-*`) — run `npm run tokens:build` after JSON changes |
| `src/styles/typography.css` | Typography utility classes |
| `src/index.css` | ShadCN ↔ token mapping (`--background`, `--primary`, etc.) |

## Colors — use these

**Tailwind semantic classes (preferred):**
- `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `bg-muted`, `bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-primary`, `border-border`, `ring-ring`

**Raw token variables (when semantic classes are not enough):**
- `var(--sys-primary)`, `var(--sys-on-surface)`, `var(--sys-accent-container)`, etc.

## Typography — use these

Use typography utilities, not ad-hoc `text-xl font-semibold`:

- `.type-display1`, `.type-display2` — Cormorant Garamond headings
- `.type-title1`, `.type-title1-em`, `.type-title2`, `.type-title3-em`
- `.type-body1`, `.type-body2`
- `.type-caption1-uppercase`, `.type-caption2`

## Elevation

- `.shadow-elevation-1` — cards, project links
- `.shadow-elevation-2` — modals, password gate, hover states

## Do NOT use (unless user requests a design change)

- Hardcoded hex/rgb/oklch in components (e.g. `#f7f8fa`, `bg-neutral-950`)
- Tailwind default palette for UI (`neutral-*`, `sky-*`, `slate-*`, `zinc-*`, etc.)
- Arbitrary values like `text-[#00749b]` or `bg-[#ffffff]`
- Re-defining colors in `index.css` without updating `tokens.json` first

## When tokens need to change

1. Update `Design-tokens/tokens.json` (from Figma)
2. Run `npm run tokens:build`
3. Use existing semantic classes — avoid editing generated CSS by hand

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div className="bg-neutral-950 text-white">
<h1 className="text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-400">

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="bg-background text-foreground">
<h1 className="type-display2 text-foreground">
<p className="type-body1 text-muted-foreground">
```
